this most beautiful creation of theirs.</p>\r\n<p>We are now the proud owners of a few Anton Smit sculptures, to remind us forever of his genius, his passion to share it with the world and above-all, his humility.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>REINHARD AND MARGRET KÜNSTLER AND INGA AND CHRISTIAN</strong></p>\r\n<p>We – as a family – would like to express how happy and proud we are, not only to know Anton, but also to enjoy our long lasting friendship with him. He is such a special person and gifted artist.</p>\r\n<p>What started out as a very fruitful business relationship during my time at BMW SA, e.g. the wonderful sculptures for the Midrand office and Anton’s support for the 5-series launch in 1996, turned into a very personal, special friendship. Anton’s vision, passion, enthusiasm and energy are impressive and his warm-hearted, giving personality is overwhelming.</p>\r\n<p>Being back in Germany, we organised together several exhibitions of Anton’s outstanding art in Wolfsburg, Essen, Leer and Hamburg, and shared wonderful moments.</p>\r\n<p>We love and admire Anton, always enjoy his company and his wonderful sense of humour. We wish him for the years to come that all his plans and wishes come true and we look forward to being part of it.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\r\n<p><strong>ANDRÉ CLEMENTS</strong></p>\r\n<p>As I recall it was a Friday afternoon, in autumn I think, about twenty years ago when I rocked up uninvited at Anton’s front gate in a dilapidated Toyota bakkie. I rang the bell and Anton opened the gate with a running hosepipe in his hand. I explained that I had come across some of his sculptures and that they had made a deep impression on me. I told him I had looked up his address in the phonebook and just wanted to tell him that I liked his work. Rather than being freaked out by this weird stranger, Anton invited me into his garden where he was spraying down the footpath meandering between a host