\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"354\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/3\"][vc_single_image image=\"356\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','COLOSSAL HEAD','','inherit','open','open','','346-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:04:51','2014-10-24 13:04:51','',346,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/346-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(683,1,'2014-10-24 15:07:47','2014-10-24 13:07:47','<p>[vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text]</p>\r\n<p>This sculpture was inspired by Proverbs 8, Wisdom\'s Call. Herewith a small extract: <sup>22</sup> The Lord brought me forth as the first of his works, before his deeds of old; <sup>23</sup> I was formed long ages ago, at the very beginning, when the world came to be. <sup>24</sup> When there were no watery depths, I was given birth, when there were no springs overflowing with water; <sup>25</sup> before the mountains were settled in place, before the hills, I was given birth, <sup>26</sup> before he made the world or its fields or any of the dust of the earth. <sup>27</sup> I was there when he set the heavens in place, when he marked out the horizon on the face of the deep, <sup>28</sup> when he established the clouds above and fixed securely the fountains of the deep, <sup>29</sup> when he gave the sea its boundary so the waters would not overstep his command, and when he marked out the foundations of the earth.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"316\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','THE BEGINNING<br />OF WISDOM','','inherit','open','open','','314-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:07:47','2014-10-24 13:07:47','',314,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/314-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(684,1,'2014-10-24 15:08:32','2014-10-24 13:08:32','<p>[vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"fgj-textblock\"]</p>\r\n<p>This sculpture was inspired by Proverbs 8, Wisdom\'s Call. Herewith a small extract:</p>\r\n<p><sup>22</sup> The Lord brought me forth as the first of his works, before his deeds of old; <sup>23</sup> I was formed long ages ago, at the very beginning, when the world came to be. <sup>24</sup> When there were no watery depths, I was given birth, when there were no springs overflowing with water; <sup>25</sup> before the mountains were settled in place, before the hills, I was given birth, <sup>26</sup> before he made the world or its fields or any of the dust of the earth. <sup>27</sup> I was there when he set the heavens in place, when he marked out the horizon on the face of the deep, <sup>28</sup> when he established the clouds above and fixed securely the fountains of the deep, <sup>29</sup> when he gave the sea its boundary so the waters would not overstep his command, and when he marked out the foundations of the earth.</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_single_image image=\"316\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','THE BEGINNING<br />OF WISDOM','','inherit','open','open','','314-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:08:32','2014-10-24 13:08:32','',314,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/314-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(685,1,'2014-10-24 15:09:36','2014-10-24 13:09:36','<p>[vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"312\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"310\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_single_image image=\"577\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','DIE VERLANGE','','inherit','open','open','','307-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:09:36','2014-10-24 13:09:36','',307,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/307-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(686,1,'2014-10-24 15:13:12','2014-10-24 13:13:12','<p>[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1413794564444{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"fgj-textblock\"]</p>\r\n<p>\"There was a posed studio photograph done in the 40\'s post-war sepia toned style of my mother looking up, her face awash in a mystical heavenly light.</p>\r\n<p>After passing away in 1981, she was cremated in Durban and her ashes somehow got lost. I was overwhelmed with a sense of unbearable loss and vented my grief on a sculpture, in a trance like state until my brother walked into the studio and exclaimed: \"Oh I see you’ve made a scultpure of mom’s photo, what a remarkable resemblance.\"</p>\r\n<p>Ever since then I have always kept that sculpture outside my studio as a memorial to my mother, so instead of occasionally visiting her grave, she is with me every day.\"</p>\r\n<p>- Anton Smit -</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_single_image image=\"295\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','KATHERINA','','inherit','open','open','','294-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:13:12','2014-10-24 13:13:12','',294,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/294-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(687,1,'2014-10-24 15:13:56','2014-10-24 13:13:56','<p>[vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_single_image image=\"201\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>','COLOSSAL YOUTH BLACK','','inherit','open','open','','199-revision-v1','','','2014-10-24 15:13:56','2014-10-24 13:13:56','',199,'http://192.168.1.11/ANTONSMIT/website/htdocs/199-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(688,1,'2014-10-24 15:17:19','2014-10-24 13:17:19','<p>[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1413464251508{margin-bottom: 0px !important;}\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"fgj-textblock\"]</p>\r\n<p>\"Every time the sculpture became vandalised, they had to re-plaster it. But after the constant refurbishing, the gallery decided that it would be easier to paint it white. As soon as they painted it white; I saw the sculpture as an open canvas. I decided to \'vandalise\' the sculpture in my own way. But instead, paint it in a fresh and exciting way for the public to re-discover.</p>\r\n<p>As the years passed on, the sculpture became a platform for me to conceptually experiment with. I once wrapped it with plastic covering. Also, I used plastered sand and covered the statue with a simple line relief. My memories of the sculpture was an important stage in my artistic development; and I considered it as my first step into the public art. I hope Anton and I can one day collaborate again.\"</p>\r\n<p>- Roan Hendrikz -</p>\r\n<p>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"170\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"238\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"custom-grid\"][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"168\" alignment=\"center\" border_color=\"grey\" img_link_target=\"_self\" img_size=\"blog-thumb\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"169\" ali